    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka shares move up over 1-pct in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka shares gained over 1 percent in mid-day trade on Tuesday (02) for the fifth consecutive session, Colombo Stock Exchange data showed.",
        "The main index gained over 1.47 percent or 113.83 points to 7,882.40 at 1130 hours.",
        "\u201cWe are seeing positivity coming into the market in the new month as we get closer towards a possible IMF program,\u201d a top market analyst said.",
        "\u201cYesterday\u2019s price revision is also working well with Lanka IOC being a driver in the market\u2019s gain. There is some progress in some economic reforms meanwhile we are seeing good earning in dollar companies.\u201d",
        "Most liquid S&P SL20 index gained 1.68 percent or 41.01 points to 2,486.10."
      ],
